comments.body:
@edsantiago oh, maybe a solution to help soften the hard-coding:  Add comment pointing to: 
https://cloud.google.com/vpc/docs/vpc#ip-ranges

(the "default" VPC network for all new projects in google is auto-mode).

@edsantiago FWIW: for me, my misunderstanding was re:

>  'hopelessly confused. If I can try one last time'

I read that like a request for help and more explanation instead of a change suggestion. That disabled my detail-radar as I searched your comment for clues why you were confused.  Suggestion: Maybe something like this would have been more clear: "Can we simplify the big list down to just 10.128.0.0/9, since it covers the same range, and is documented as reserved?"
